node.text:
Spotting the rare pink dolphin 🐬💖

While we’re not sure whether this video was edited or not, pink dolphins actually exist. The endangered Amazon river dolphin and Indo-Pacific humpback dolphin both have a pink shade to them (especially males). Have you heard of them before?

Via: discoverearth

node.text:
Helpless turtle gets rescued 🐢 

Join Brodie Moss and the crew as they explore the remote islands of Australia. This time of year brings in hundreds of mating turtles to the shallows. Right place at the right time allowed the crew to rescue a washed up helpless turtle stuck on her back.
Video by: @brodiemoss 
Music by: Julius Dreisig & Zeus X Crona - Invisible provided by NoCopyrightSounds 🎶
